5.)📚 What I Learned Today
manage.py, wsgi.py, and asgi.py are different entry points into the same Django application.
DJANGO_SETTINGS_MODULE tells each entry point which configuration to load.
Django cannot initialize without knowing its settings module.
Staging environments provide confidence before production deployments.


6.) 📚 What I Learned Today
Relative imports (from .base import *) tell Python to import from the current package.
Wildcard imports are generally discouraged, but they are an accepted pattern for Django settings because the goal is to inherit and override configuration.
Configuration drift occurs when duplicated environment settings slowly become inconsistent.
Every structural refactor should be followed immediately by a verification step.
